		<AccordionItem title="Are hearing aid fittings covered by insurance?">
			<p>
				Coverage really depends on your individual insurance plan. While
				Medicare typically does not cover hearing aids or fittings, some
				private insurance plans or hearing benefit programs may offer
				coverage. Because every plan is different, we take care of contacting
				your insurance provider directly to check your specific benefits and
				help you understand what may be available to you. Our goal is to make
				this process as simple and stress-free as possible so you can focus on
				your hearing, not the paperwork.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="How can I make my hearing aids more comfortable?">
			<p>
				Comfort is incredibly important, and you should never feel like you
				just have to "put up with" something that doesn't feel right. If your
				hearing aids are causing any discomfort, whether it's the fit, the
				sound, or how they feel throughout the day, please let us know. Often,
				small adjustments to the fit or programming can make a big difference.
				In some cases, we may also recommend custom earmolds designed
				specifically for your ears to improve both comfort and stability.
				We're here to make sure your hearing aids feel as natural and easy to
				wear as possible.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="How long does a hearing aid fitting take?">
			<p>
				Your initial hearing aid fitting typically takes about an hour. During
				that time, we focus on making sure your devices are properly
				programmed, comfortable, and that you feel confident using them before
				you leave. Because adjustment is a process, we also schedule a few
				follow-up visits to fine-tune your settings based on your real-world
				experiences. These check-ins are an important part of helping your
				hearing aids truly work their best for you in everyday life.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>

